8. Key Findings

8.1 The Idea Is Not the Work

The idea is the beginning of the work. Confusing it with the work is like mistaking a restaurant menu for dinner and then complaining that the soup is flat.

8.2 AI Can Produce Blueprints Faster Than Reality Can Approve Them

Artificial intelligence may accelerate concept generation, visualisation, drafting assistance, documentation, and iteration. It does not repeal friction, heat, tooling, standards, fatigue, material cost, solder failure, bearing wear, or gravity.

Gravity remains notably non-disruptable.

8.3 Engineering Is the Discipline of Being Interrupted by Facts

The engineer’s job is not to betray the vision. The engineer’s job is to prevent the vision from collapsing into litigation.

8.4 Tolerances Are Civilisation

Without tolerances, assembly becomes theology. Every part must be believed in rather than measured.

8.5 A Machine Is a Negotiated Settlement

A working machine is the outcome of negotiation between intention and matter. Neither side gets everything it wants.

