11. Concluding Statement

The blueprint is not the machine.

The machine is not the idea.

The idea is not the product.

The product is not the render.

The render is not the prototype.

The prototype is not the production unit.

The production unit is not the fielded system.

The fielded system is not the thing the customer will do to it.

This paper has therefore demonstrated that between concept and machine lies an enormous territory of labour, measurement, compromise, correction, and consequence. The tech bro generation, in its understandable excitement, has often mistaken the first sentence of this process for the final chapter.

However, in the interest of administrative balance, the Committee concludes that the blueprint should henceforth be treated as a fully realised machine, provided that no one attempts to build, power, certify, sell, repair, ship, assemble, test, touch, drop, update, clean, or use it.
